<h1> There are over many species of plants around the world, beneficial to our body, bringing good health. </h1>
<h3> Drinking flower tea can be one of the best treatments for indigestion, constipation,
acid reflux and many other ailments related to the digestive system. </h3>
</main>
<h3> Some of the best flower teas to drink for digestion are peppermint, chrysanthemum, rose and ginger. </h3>
<h3> Peppermint </h3> 
<img src="Mint.jpeg">

Peppermint can help improve digestion, freshen breath and improve concentration. 
In addition, this mint has antibacterial properties and can improve allergy symptoms, headaches and blocked airways.
<h3> Chrysanthemum </h3> 
<img src="chrysanthemum.jpeg">

Chrysanthemum tea helps lower blood pressure, cool the body, and reduce inflammation, all of which can help induce calmness. 
The powerful antioxidants and minerals in the infusion can help your body regulate itself better and remove unnecessary stress hormones from your bloodstream.
<h3> Rose petals </h3>
<img src="Rose tea.jpeg">

Rose petals contain polyphenols, antioxidants that work to protect your body from cell damage. 
The polyphenols in rose tea have been shown to reduce the risk of heart disease, diabetes, obesity, and cognitive diseases.
<h3> Ginger </h3>
<img src="Ginger.jpeg">

Ginger tea can have benefits for digestion, inflammation and the common cold.
